-- France’s Baroin Says Worst of Euro Crisis Is Probably Over
-- B y   M a r k   D e e n
-- 2012-03-13T19:06:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-13/france-s-baroin-says-worst-of-euro-crisis-is-probably-over-1-.html
French Finance Minister  Francois Baroin  said the worst of  Europe ’s debt crisis is probably over.  “If the question is, ‘Is the worst of the crisis over?’
the answer is ‘yes,” Baroin said at a conference in Paris.  Speaking at the same event, German Finance Minister
 Wolfgang Schaeuble  said that there is “more than a 50 percent
probability” that the worst of the crisis has passed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mark Deen in Paris at 
